The paper deals with image inpainting, which is a computer vision task, and proposes a new approach using deep generative models. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel block-wise procedural training scheme and adversarial loss annealing, which are related to deep learning techniques and optimization, respectively, suggesting cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of conditional generative adversarial networks (conditional GANs), which is a popular technique in generative models and falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses several losses specifically designed for inpainting, which is related to graphics and visualization, indicating cs.GR (Graphics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper demonstrates the practical value of the proposed framework for interactive guided inpainting, which is related to multimedia and falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
